          <h2>Horizontally Aligning</h2>
          <p>Horizontally aligning a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> is more easier than vertically aligning a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>.</p>
          <h3>Auto Margin</h3>
          <p>A margin sets the space outside the selected element. Setting the element's left and right margin to auto, automatically makes it centered horizontally. </p>
          <p>Your code should contain <code>margin-left: auto;</code> and <code>margin-right: auto;</code>, and it's <code>display</code> must be set to <code>block</code> using <code>display: block;</code>.</p>
